2. Inheritance: Inheritance is a mechanism where an object can inherit properties and behaviors from its parent class. This allows code reuse and makes it easier to maintain and scale the system.

Examples of Inheritance in Java:

class BankAccount {
  private int accountNumber;
  private double balance;

  public BankAccount(int accountNumber, double balance) {
    this.accountNumber = accountNumber;
    this.balance = balance;
  }

  public int getAccountNumber() {
    return accountNumber;
  }

  public double getBalance() {
    return balance;
  }
}

class SavingsAccount extends BankAccount {
  private double interestRate;

  public SavingsAccount(int accountNumber, double balance, double interestRate) {
    super(accountNumber, balance);
    this.interestRate = interestRate;
  }

  public double getInterestRate() {
    return interestRate;
  }
}

